rComments: A great professor to have if you are interested in cinema or German culture. Not too difficult to do well if you put in some work, and understand the learning objectives.
Very engaging professor. Provided a lot of different and thought-provoking perspectives on the material. Detailed assignments guidelines were very helpful.
An absolute joy. Prof. Fenner loves film, loves students and loves the material. Friendly, approachable, laid back, and very sharp.

this is a very eccentric woman...which is a great thing, she is quite easy going but her class is more like a discussion then a class which is good if you like that kinda thing, and not so much if you don't.
A great class, always keeps class focused and encourages class discussion. One of the best classes I've had all 4 years of school!

course is geared way more towards film students - i'm not one and i get left behind alot in discussions but i'm still learning some interesting things. readings are more dense than expected. prof encourages discussion, whch is good. overall, a good course
